          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The deuteron beam current was about from 2.5 to",
                "3.5 uA. The length and pressure of the deuterium gas",
                "target were 2.0 cm and 0.30 MPa. For neutrons with",
                "energy of 4.0, 4.5 and 5.0 MeV, the energies were",
                "0.21, 0.19 and 0.16 MeV, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A twin gridded ionization chamber (GIC) was",
                "used as the charged particle detector with forward",
                "and backward asymmetrical sections."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The BF3 counter was used as the neutron flux",
                "monitor."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "5-B-10",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.94
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 10B sample consists of four",
                "components: the 10B deposit, the aluminum-film",
                "backing as the substrate of 10B deposit, the tantalum",
                "frame bearing the aluminum backing, and the aluminum",
                "washer to fix and flatten the tantalum frame. In",
                "addition to the 10B sample, a thin-film background",
                "sample was also prepared without the 10B deposits on",
                "the aluminum backing which was used for the",
                "background measurement."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "3-LI-6",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.9
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The reference 6LiF sample was also",
                "prepared and the lithium fluoride was evaporated onto",
                "a tantalum-foil backing (48.0 mm x 0.1 mm) without",
                "holes.",
                "The number of 10B atoms was determined by the relative",
                "comparison method using the thermal neutron induced",
                "10B(nth,a)7Li and 6Li(nth,t)4He reactions with a 6LiF",
                "sample as the reference."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "92-U-238",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.99997
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The mass and the diameter of",
                "the 238U sample were 493.6 ug/cm2 and 4.50 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cross sections of the 10B(n,t2a) and 10B(n,a)7Li",
                "reactions were calculated using the event counts from",
                "the spectrum unfolding method and the residual",
                "method. The residual method was taken as the final",
                "results since the event counts obtained by the",
                "residual method are more accurate. The event counts",
                "from the (n,t2a) and (n,a) can be separated on the a",
                "energy spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "92-U-238(N,F),,SIG",
